                              <item>
                                 <p>Vellum, about 9 5/8 in. by 6 5/8, consisting of 48 leaves, many of
                                    which are slightly stained by water. Fol. 9 is also otherwise
                                    mutilated. The quires, of which the original signatures are no
                                    longer apparent, are now only 5 in number; but one is wanting at
                                    the beginning of the volume, another at the end, and probably
                                    more than one after fol. 20. Each page is divided into two
                                    columns, of from 32 to 37 lines.</p>
                              </item>
                           </list>
